on Tonya Harding. However, Mr. Dwyre does not know what he is talking about 
when he places the blame on Harding's lawyers and the legal system. 
</P>
<P>
 Dwyre says: "Tonya Harding might be the greatest bonanza to billable hours in 
the history of the State of Oregon." Tonya's lawyers accomplished for their 
client the ultimate 100% victory with a bare minimum of billable hours. In 
reaching this victory in a very short time, the lawyers very likely cut 
themselves out of a fee of $10 million or so, to which they would have been 
entitled on a recovery of a $25-million judgment. 
