<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIVISION III-AA ROUNDUP; HENDERSON'S 22 POINTS KEY MAGNOLIA VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT JONES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Senior point guard Frank Henderson scored 22 points and had nine rebounds to 
lead Magnolia to a 52-47 victory over Newport Harbor at Magnolia in a Division 
III-AA boys' basketball playoff game Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Magnolia will meet Servite in Tuesday's quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sentinels (19-7) trailed, 12-10, after one quarter, but outscored the 
Sailors, 15-6, in the second quarter to take a 25-18 halftime lead. Magnolia, 
which recorded its 17th consecutive home victory, extended the lead to 11 
points, 29-18, early in the third quarter. But Newport Harbor (13-14) fought 
back, cutting the lead to four on Will Rankin's basket early in the fourth 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 "I thought we were in control with that lead, but we didn't play good defense 
and they stayed with us," Magnolia Coach Al Wallin said. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor played without starting center Ramy Shoukry, who underwent an 
emergency appendectomy Monday. His replacement, John Giordani, was brought up 
from the junior varsity. He responded by scoring 11 points, all in the second 
half, to keep the Sailors close. 
</P>
<P>
 Magnolia's LaShawn Neal sealed the victory, scoring two key baskets in the 
last 1:30 and blocking two shots. 
</P>
<P>
 "Getting this first game out of the way is always tough. I was pleased with 
our performance tonight," Wallin said. 
</P>
<P>
 Paul Tayyar led Newport Harbor with 12 points. SCOTT JONES 
</P>
