<TEXT>
<P>
 Olujimi Mann scored Santa Ana Valley's last 11 points, including the 
game-winning free throw with four seconds left, as the Falcons defeated Long 
Beach Jordan, 51-50, Friday in a Southern Section Division I-AA second-round 
playoff game. 
</P>
<P>
 After Mann blocked a potential game-winning shot by Jordan's Chris Sykes with 
10 seconds left, he got the rebound and was fouled in the backcourt by Jordan's 
Robert Masing.Mann made the front end of a one-and-one, then Jordan's Brandon 
Boyd launched a half-court shot that bounced off the backboard and rim to end 
the game.  
</P>
<P>
 Mann, who finished with 27 points, made two free throws with 20.4 seconds left 
to tie the score at 50. The sophomore guard rallied Santa Ana Valley (25-3) 
from a 48-42 deficit with two minutes left by making two three-pointers.  
</P>
<P>
