<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION DIVISION I-AA BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; FOUNTAIN VALLEY STOPS 
ESPERANZA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM BIRSCHBACH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fountain Valley combined consistent field-goal and free-throw shooting with 
solid defense to defeat Esperanza, 57-45, in the second round of the Southern 
Section Division I-AA boys' basketball playoffs Friday night at Esperanza High 
School. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sunset League champion Barons (22-5) led from the opening minutes behind 
57.1% shooting from the floor and 15-of-17 shooting from the free-throw line, 
including seven of eight down the stretch by guard Danny Hoppie.The Barons play 
Long Beach Poly in Tuesday's quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 "We played real well defensively," Fountain Valley Coach Gordon Billingsley 
said. "I'm real happy to be where we are. Everything is icing on the cake. We 
really came together as a team and played well together tonight." 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza (18-9) made a run at Fountain Valley and trailed after three 
quarters, 40-34, on Mike Lawson's turnaround shot in the key with four seconds 
remaining in the quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 But Baron reserve guard Dave Arvesen, playing extensively for the first time 
in four games since injuring a tooth against Huntington Beach, hit a basket, 
two free throws and a three-point field goal with 6:12 remaining to open up a 
47-36 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley center Phil Domingo led all scorers with 17 points on 
eight-of-11 shooting. Lawson led Esperanza with 16 points. TOM BIRSCHBACH 
</P>
</TEXT>
