<P>
DIVISION IV BOYS' BASKETBALL; WHITTIER CHRISTIAN IS KNOCKED OFF BY DOWNEY PIUS 
X 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RUSSELL BANKS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Downey Pius X finished in a three-way tie for third place in the Del Rey 
League and won the coin flip, thanks, in part, to the call of Principal Michael 
Parmer. 
</P>
<P>
 The Warriors (12-12) then went out and upended highly regarded Whittier 
Christian, 68-56, in the opening round of the IV-A playoffs Friday at Los 
Angeles Chiropractic College. 
</P>
<P>
 "He beat me to the coin flip," Pius X Coach Deon Evans said. 
</P>
<P>
 That turned out to be good for Pius X, but bad for Whittier Christian (21-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Downey Pius X put on a three-point shooting exhibition, especially in the 
second half, behind the likes of Allen Fletcher, Marcel Yates and Robert 
Hargrove. 
</P>
<P>
 Fletcher finished with 17 points, Yates had 16 and Hargrove 11. 
</P>
<P>
 When the three weren't hurting Whittier Christian's defense from the outside, 
6-foot-7 Troy Collins did the damage inside and finished with 16 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Tyler Ream scored a game-high 23 points for Whittier Christian, including all 
12 of the Heralds' points in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Kwadwo Bochie had 15. RUSSELL BANKS 
