</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bob McClung scored a game-high 24 points and Dave Vaccaro was three blocks 
away from a triple-double to lead Liberty Christian past Pacific Shores, 70-42, 
in a second-round Southern Section Division V-A boys' basketball playoff game 
at Laguna Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Vaccaro scored 18 points, grabbed 11 rebounds and blocked seven shots, leading 
the Minutemen (14-11) to Tuesday's quarterfinals against No. 1-seeded Santa 
Maria Valley Christian. 
</P>
<P>
 Vaccaro scored 11 of Liberty's 19 first-quarter points, and 15 of the team's 
33 in the first half, as the Minutemen opened a 33-19 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 "Dave Vaccaro came to play," Coach Rudy Sass said. "He kept us going in the 
first half." 
</P>
<P>
 The Seahawks (10-8) were led by Roldan Chapple, with 15 points, and Danny 
Chapple (14). 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Shores got as close as 11 points when Tim Collins made a three-pointer 
to start the third quarter, but Liberty scored the next eight points to open a 
41-22 lead and was never threatened again. 
</P>
