EDISON UPSETS TOP-SEEDED SIMI VALLEY ROYAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Under hail, rain and eventually sunshine, Edison took control early and upset 
top-seeded Simi Valley Royal, 4-2, in the first round of the Southern Section 
Division I boys' soccer playoffs Friday at Royal High. 
</P>
<P>
 "The clouds opened up and the sun started to shine on Edison's side at the end 
of the game,' Charger Coach Mike DiGiovanni said. "I guess you couldn't ask for 
a better sign than that." 
</P>
<P>
 Phil Urkov's three goals and strong team defense were the keys. Brett 
Jorgenson added the fourth goal for Edison (19-5-1), Beau Barnhart had two 
assists and Roy Ludt had four saves. 
</P>
<P>
 Royal's goals came on a penalty kick and a free kick. 
