<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION BOYS' SOCCER ROUNDUP; MARINA DEFEATS FONTANA, ADVANCES TO 
SECOND ROUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 What a difference a year can make. 
</P>
<P>
 This time last season, Marina was storing its soccer gear after missing the 
playoffs for only the second time in nine years.Meanwhile, Fontana was 
stringing together victories en route to a Southern Section boys' title. 
</P>
<P>
 Friday, it was Fontana's turn to pack up early as fourth-seeded Marina scored 
three first-half goals and defeated the Steelers, 4-1, in a Division I 
first-round game at Marina High. 
</P>
<P>
 The Vikings (16-5-1) advance to play Claremont, the Baseline League 
second-place team, in Thursday's quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 "The first playoff game is the hardest because of the nerves," Viking Coach 
David McLeish said. 
</P>
<P>
 Marina looked relaxed, taking a 1-0 lead in the opening minute when Joe 
Borzoni beat Fontana goalkeeper Omar Hernandez to his left. 
</P>
<P>
 The Vikings added to their lead 15 minutes later, when Borzoni's cross pass 
skipped past Jose Monroy, his intended target, but was knocked in by a hustling 
Jason Benwell. 
</P>
<P>
 Benwell scored again in the first half when he used his knee to direct a cross 
pass into the net and Marina led comfortably, 3-0, at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 Monroy, the Vikings' leading scorer, scored the fourth goal when he made a 
pair of fancy moves around two Steeler defenders and hit the corner of the net 
with a shot off his left foot. 
</P>
<P>
 Fontana finished 15-7-5. DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</TEXT>
