<TEXT>
<P>
 Scott Garson scored 11 of his game-high 23 points in the first period as host 
Harvard-Westlake cruised past Workman, 88-51, in a first-round Division III-A 
playoff game Friday night at Harvard. 
</P>
<P>
 The Wolverines led, 32-8, at the end of the quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Taban (13 points) and Ben Robbins (12 points, seven assists) also scored 
in double figures for the Wolverines (23-2), who matched the school 
single-season record for victories by the boys' varsity basketball team. 
</P>
<P>
 Harvard will play Santa Paula in a second-round game on Tuesday at a site to 
be determined. 
</P>
