BRIEFLY: THE ECONOMY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Blinder Top Candidate for Fed Post: Alan Blinder, a member of President 
Clinton's economic brain trust and former Princeton University economist, is 
the leading candidate to take the No. 2 post at the Federal Reserve, 
Administration officials said.The position at the powerful central bank 
unexpectedly opened up early this month with the departure of David Mullins. 
Blinder, 48, has served the past year on the White House's Council of Economic 
Advisers. As Fed vice chairman, Blinder would play a major role in determining 
the direction of interest rates and the economy and would de facto be a top 
candidate to take over as head of the central bank when Alan Greenspan's term 
ends in 1996. 
</P>
