WEEKEND TV; A TRIO OF BLACK HISTORY MONTH SPECIALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three notable programs highlight Black History Month this weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 Set in the 1850s, "Race to Freedom: The Underground Railroad" looks at the 
efforts of four slaves who find their way to Canada -- and freedom.It stars 
Janet Bailey, Courtney Vance, Dawnn Lewis and Glynn Turman, today at 5 p.m. on 
cable's BET and again at 8 p.m. on the Family Channel. (See review below.) 
</P>
<P>
