ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FOUNTAIN VALLEY; ROCK 'JAM' TO AID ORANGEWOOD HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rock 'n' roll bands will be making music Sunday to benefit abused and 
neglected children. 
</P>
<P>
 The "Kids Benefit Jam" will be held from 2 p.m. until midnight at Music City, 
18774 Brookhurst St. 
</P>
<P>
 Proceeds from the event will benefit Orangewood Children's Home, a 
county-operated facility that provides emergency care and shelter, said Brad 
Morisette, event coordinator for the Fun Book, a recreation and entertainment 
directory that is co-sponsoring the daylong concert with Music City. 
</P>
<P>
 Morisette said the Fun Book will be coordinating a series of events this year 
to raise money for the children at the county facility. 
</P>
<P>
 "We want to create some fun and entertainment for them so it takes the trauma 
and drama out of their lives, because they're not getting a fair shake," he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Morisette said the bands and entertainers are performing free. Raffles and 
auctions will also be held, and there will be a free buffet from 2 to 8 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are $10 before the event and $13 at the door. Morisette said tickets 
are $8 at the door with a toy or item appropriate for a child or teen-ager. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information or tickets, call the Fun Book at (714) 722-1175 or Music 
City at (714) 963-2366. 
