EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; BOY PLEADS NOT GUILTY TO MURDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 13-year-old Simi Valley boy charged with fatally stabbing one of his Valley 
View Junior High School classmates pleaded not guilty in Ventura County 
Superior Court on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Judge Steven Z. Perren set an April 18 trial for Phillip Hernandez, who will 
not be tried as an adult because he is under 16. 
</P>
<P>
 Phillip is charged with a single count of murder in the Feb. 1 death of 
14-year-old Chad Patrick Hubbard, a popular student and member of the school 
baseball team. 
</P>
<P>
 Other students have said the two boys had a running feud that escalated a week 
before the stabbing when Hernandez took Chad's baseball cap. 
</P>
