<HEADLINE>
<P>
ED BEGLEY JR. JOINS BOARD OF CONSERVANCY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HUGO MARTIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Actor and environmentalist Ed Begley Jr. was unanimously confirmed Friday by 
the Los Angeles City Council to represent the city on the Santa Monica 
Mountains Conservancy board. 
</P>
<P>
 Begley, who was nominated by Mayor Richard Riordan, was appointed to the 
eight-member panel that sets policy for the conservancy, a state agency that 
buys parkland in the Santa Monica Mountains and neighboring ranges. 
</P>
<P>
 Begley, a Studio City resident who is best known for his role in the 
television series "St. Elsewhere," was previously named to the city's 
Environmental Affairs Commission, an advisory panel. 
</P>
<P>
 Speaking briefly to the council after being confirmed, Begley said he will 
"fulfill all the needs the city has" of him on the conservancy board. 
</P>
<P>
 Begley replaces Anton Calleia, a chief aide to former Mayor Tom Bradley and 
the city's representative on the conservancy board since 1982. HUGO MARTIN 
</P>
