<P>
 A jewelry store employee was shot and killed in a robbery Friday, Los Angeles 
County sheriff's deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputies responded to a 911 call at 1:11 p.m. from a person who looked into 
Charles Jewelers, at 38513 Sierra Highway, and saw smashed display cases, said 
Deputy Larry Mead of the Sheriff's Headquarters Bureau. 
</P>
<P>
 "Deputies arrived and looked through the open door and saw the store's 
employee lying on the floor," Mead said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, who was working alone at the time, was a 45-year-old man, Mead 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man's name was not released pending notification of his family. 
</P>
<P>
 An undetermined amount of jewelry was taken from the store and there were no 
clues to the identity of the killer, Mead said. 
