MAN APPARENTLY DIED OF HEART ATTACK IN FIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man who died on Valentine's Day after he was punched by the live-in friend 
of his estranged wife apparently died of a heart attack and not head injuries 
he suffered during the altercation, police said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Detectives originally believed that Charles Lovinggood, 45, died after he hit 
his head on a slate tile floor after Steven Cartrett, 29, slugged him twice 
Feb. 14. 
</P>
<P>
 Before the incident, police said Lovinggood was upset because Cartrett was 
living in a house with Marilyn Lovinggood, 45, who had been separated from her 
husband for nearly a year. 
</P>
<P>
 Marilyn Lovinggood told police that she and Cartrett were only friends and 
that Cartrett was living there because the earthquake had damaged his home. 
</P>
<P>
 Cartrett was not charged with a crime. 
</P>
<P>
 The Los Angeles County coroner's office has not released the results of 
Lovinggood's autopsy, a spokesman said. 
