<HEADLINE>
<P>
JUDGE OVERTURNS BAN ON HORSEMEN'S LOBBYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Judge Robert O'Brien of the Los Angeles Superior Court has overturned a 
California Horse Racing Board order that would have limited the ability of the 
California Horsemen's Benevolent and Protective Assn. to lobby public officials 
on issues affecting its membership. 
</P>
<P>
 At its last monthly meeting, the CHRB issued an order limiting the amount that 
could be spent on lobbying to 5% of the CHBPA's annual budget. 
</P>
<P>
 "While Judge O'Brien's decision is good news, we have little time to revel in 
our victory," CHBPA President Chris Clark said in a prepared statement Friday. 
"Our political voice has been silenced since last November and, now that the 
judge has ruled in our favor, we need to quickly press on with our legislative 
agenda." BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA021994-0264 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 015094 </DOCID>
