<P>
GRIFFINS' SOCCER PLAYOFF TO BE AT HOME TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Southern Section Division II boys' soccer first-round playoff game between 
Paramount and Los Alamitos was rescheduled to 10 a.m. today at Los Alamitos 
High because of a disturbance at the Paramount campus Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alamitos (13-7-8) is the third-seeded team from the Empire League. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Edison's Division I girls' soccer first-round game against Torrance has been 
rescheduled to 11 a.m. today instead of 3 p.m., Edison Girls' Athletic Director 
Bruce Belcher said. 
</P>
<P>
 The unseeded Chargers (23-4-1) finished the regular season ranked second in 
Orange County behind Marina, the top-seeded team in Division I. 
</P>
</TEXT>
