<P>
PREP BASKETBALL PLAYOFFS; MATER DEI BREEZES PAST ARROYO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Top-ranked Santa Ana Mater Dei used well-balanced scoring in a 90-39, Southern 
Section Division I-A, second-round victory over El Monte Arroyo at the UC 
Irvine Bren Center Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei's Clay McKnight and Miles Simon each scored 21 points, Schea Cotton 
added 19 and Shaun Jackson 16. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei (28-0) took a 56-20 halftime lead over Arroyo (21-6). McKnight made 
five three-pointers and Simon had 11 assists and four three-pointers. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 6 Inglewood 80, Rosemead 50 -- Paul Pierce scored 26 points and Ray Outler 
15 to lead Inglewood (24-3) to a Division II-AA, first-round victory over 
Rosemead (14-10) at Inglewood. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 7 Riverside J.W. North 61, Claremont 46 -- Brian Hooks scored 23 points to 
lead J.W. North (25-0) in a Division II-AA, first-round victory over Claremont 
(11-16) at J.W. North. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 8 Bellflower St. John Bosco 79, West Torrance 61 -- Jelani Gardner scored 
31 points, including 20 in the second half, to lead St. John Bosco (24-2) in a 
Division II-A, first-round victory over West Torrance (11-14) at St. John 
Bosco. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 13 Los Alamitos 74, Bell Gardens 53 -- Tim Lin scored 25 points, including 
six three-pointers, to lead Los Alamitos (22-4) over Bell Gardens (21-7) in a 
Division I-AA, second-round game at Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 14 Loyola 68, Saugus 47 -- Brothers Toby and Moose Bailey each scored a 
game-high 18 points as Mission League champion Loyola (20-5) defeated Saugus 
(11-11) in a Division I-A, second-round playoff game. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 18 Santa Ana Valley 51, Long Beach Jordan 50 -- Olujimi Mann scored 27 
points and made the winning free throw with four seconds remaining to lift 
Santa Ana Valley (25-3) to a Division I-AA, second-round victory at Jordan 
(11-13). 
</P>
<P>
 In other games: Ty Berry scored 19 points to lead Ayala (22-4) to a 55-32, 
Division I-AA, second-round victory over Alhambra (15-11) at Ayala. . . . 
Richard Diaz scored a game-high 29 points and Michael Batiste had 28 to carry 
Long Beach Wilson (21-7) to a 92-88, overtime victory against Canyon Country 
Canyon (20-7) in a Division I-AA, second-round game at Wilson. 
</P>
