<TEXT>
<P>
 Pope John Paul II may return to the United States this year, on a lightning 
East Coast visit. 
</P>
<P>
 Vatican sources said Friday the 73-year-old pontiff hopes to address the 
United Nations in New York as it observes its 50th anniversary. 
</P>
<P>
 Planning is incomplete, but the late October stop in New York could be 
followed by short pastoral visits to Newark, N.J., and Baltimore, the sources 
said. 
