<P>
MARLA TRUMP'S EX-PUBLICIST TOLD TO WEAR ELECTRONIC BRACELET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Marla Trump's former publicist was ordered Friday to wear an electronic 
bracelet while he appeals his conviction for burglarizing her home and stealing 
her shoes and underwear. 
</P>
<P>
 Judge Richard Andrias said he believes Chuck Jones "is a very troubled person" 
but disagreed with a prosecutor that he has violent tendencies. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to wearing the bracelet, Andrias ordered Jones to secure bond with 
the deed to his Greenwich, Conn., home, valued at about $800,000. 
</P>
