and weapon possession. He faces 1 1/2 years to 15 years in prison on the 
burglary count alone. Sentencing is set for April 6. 
</P>
<P>
 The electronic bracelet allows correction officials to monitor Jones' 
movements while he is under house arrest. The judge said he can leave home only 
to go to work or to attend to legal matters. 
