<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES COUNTY; 
DEADLINE FOR QUAKE AID APPLICATIONS EXTENDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The deadline for nonprofit organizations that sustained earthquake damage to 
apply for disaster assistance has been extended to until March 18. 
</P>
<P>
 The Federal Emergency Management Agency offers various forms of disaster 
assistance to nonprofit organizations and individuals, and damage need not have 
occurred on Jan. 17 to be covered. 
</P>
<P>
 To register potential claims with FEMA, call (800) 462-9029 or the California 
Office of Emergency Services at (818) 405-7350. 
</P>
