<TEXT>
<P>
 Sophomore guard Nick Punto scored 23 points to lead Trabuco Hills to an 85-70 
victory over Woodbridge in the opening round of the Division II-AA boys' 
basketball playoffs Friday at Trabuco Hills High. 
</P>
<P>
 Punto made seven three-pointers for the Mustangs (22-5). 
</P>
<P>
 Junior forward Rob Warnick added 18 points and senior Ryan Karnoff scored 17 
and grabbed 12 rebounds for Trabuco Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior guard Chris Talbott scored 15 points to lead Woodbridge (11-15). 
</P>
<P>
 Senior guard Adam Libby added 14 points and connected on three three-pointers 
for Woodbridge. 
</P>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills led 44-31 at halftime and moved out to 67-47 advantage after 
three quarters. 
</P>
<P>
 But Woodbridge closed the gap to 76-68 on Libby's three-pointer with 2:45 left 
in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 But Trabuco Hills went on a 9-0 run to move ahead, 85-68, with 40 seconds left 
in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills will face Huntington Beach in the next round. 
</P>
