By MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Katella survived 29 turnovers and the loss of starting point guard Tommy 
Burfeind early in the game to hold off Valencia, 44-41, in the first round of 
the Southern Section Division II-A boys' basketball playoffs Friday night at 
Valencia. 
</P>
<P>
 Katella will play host to Tustin Tuesday in the quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 The Knights led all the way, but Valencia made it close, making the score 
41-40 when Jason Miele hit a three-point basket with 29.4 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 A foul away from the shot and two free throws by Mike Pahl gave Katella a 
43-40 edge. 
</P>
<P>
 Burfeind, making his first start, suffered a dislocated knee with 6:50 left in 
the first quarter. He was the third person to start at point guard for Katella 
(16-8) this year. 
</P>
<P>
 Katella held a 27-16 lead after three quarters in a low-scoring defensive 
struggle before Valencia upped the tempo in the final quarter, scoring 25 only 
to come up short. Valencia forced 11 Katella turnovers in the final quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 LaByron Clayton with 15 points and Pahl with 10 led Katella's scoring while 
Jermaine Gray with 11 and Junior Alatorre with 10 paced the Tigers (18-11). 
