<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION DIVISION IV BOYS' SOCCER; SUNNY HILLS CAN'T PREVENT HISTORY 
FROM REPEATING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE McKIBBEN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sunny Hills Coach Mike Schade has to be wondering what he did to the Southern 
Section seeding committee to deserve this. 
</P>
<P>
 Five years of playing Sea View teams in the first round, five losses. The 
latest, a 3-1 defeat Friday to Saddleback in the Southern Section Division IV 
boys' soccer playoffs in Santa Ana, was closer than it appeared. Nonetheless, 
Sunny Hills' season is over, courtesy of the Sea View League. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was standing here last year in about this same spot talking to reporters 
about our troubles with the Sea View League," Schade said. "Sunny Hills played 
a great game (Friday)." 
</P>
<P>
 Just not quite great enough. 
</P>
<P>
 Sunny Hills took a 1-0 lead six minutes into the second half on a spectacular 
Chris Roselli goal off a nice feed from Nick Walton. But it evaporated 12 
minutes later when sweeper Oscar Cisneros lined a shot, from about 30 yards 
out, past a diving Jeff Murphy. The goal even appeared to shock Cisneros. 
</P>
<P>
 "The coach told me I had to go up, because we had to pressure them," Cisneros 
said. "My partner (Juan Arreola) kicked it right to me and I just hit it. It 
was some 20 meters out. I couldn't believe it." 
</P>
<P>
 Within 10 minutes, Saddleback was on the board again when Ramon Alvarado 
rebounded Abdias Avila's shot. Juan Maldonado finished the scoring with three 
minutes left when he scored off a throw-in from Avila. 
</P>
<P>
 "It seems like when the other team scores on us, the kids really pick up the 
tempo," Saddleback Coach Mel Silva said. "Our league is so tough. We've been 
behind before to good teams and pulled games out." 
</P>
<P>
 Schade said he saw the Saddleback outburst coming, but he felt helpless in 
trying to stop it. 
</P>
<P>
 "With the depth of their team and they're so big and strong up front, I knew 
it was just a matter of time," Schade said. "They just have too much 
firepower." 
</P>
<P>
 In other Division IV games: 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra 4, Norwalk 1 -- Hugo Estrella, Miguel Garcia, John Mendrin and Mark 
Lamb each scored and Javier Flores had four saves for La Habra (11-5-5), which 
handed Norwalk (14-1-2) its first loss of the season. 
</P>
<P>
 The Highlanders will play the winner of La Verne Bonita-San Bernardino Cajon 
in the second round Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Margarita 2, Moreno Valley Valley View 0 -- Chon Kantikovit and Matt 
Blasdel each scored and Brian Casola and Mike Greco each had two saves to lead 
visiting Santa Margarita (14-4-5). Santa Margarita will play the winner of 
Corona Centennial-La Mirada in the second round on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Sonora 2, Lakewood Mayfair 1 (3 OT) -- Chris Fernandez scored off a penalty 
kick in the third overtime to give Sonora the victory. Fernandez scored both 
goals for Sonora (16-3-3). His first goal came off an assist assist by Paul 
Copeland five minutes into the game. Mayfair tied the score, 1-1, with 23 
minutes remaining in the first half on a crossing header by Joe Gritl. Mayfair 
finishes 13-8-4. 
</P>
