CORONA DEL MAR UPSET BY CORONA IN FIRST ROUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Corona del Mar, Orange County's top-ranked boys' soccer team, was knocked from 
the Division IV playoffs Friday when Corona pulled off a 2-1 upset in a 
first-round game at Corona del Mar High. 
</P>
<P>
 Sea View League champion Corona del Mar was seeded fourth in the division. 
Corona was the No. 3 team in the Mountain View League and an unseeded wild-card 
team. 
</P>
<P>
 But Corona (16-5-3), which defeated Arlington, 2-1, Wednesday to get its shot 
at the Sea Kings, got second-half goals by Joey Digiamarino and Louis Gonzales. 
Corona del Mar finished 19-3-4. 
