<HEADLINE>
<P>
CYPRESS' DROUGHT ALLOWS RIVERSIDE TO CLINCH TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cypress went six minutes of the second half without a point, allowing 
Riverside to clinch the Orange Empire Conference men's basketball title with a 
79-70 victory Friday at Riverside. 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside's victory, coupled with Irvine Valley's 81-80 upset of Saddleback, 
allowed the Tigers (26-6, 12-2) to win the conference title outright. It is 
their first championship since 1989. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress (15-18, 6-8) trailed for the first 26 minutes but fought back to take 
a seven-point lead with 10 minutes left. Then came the scoring drought. 
</P>
<P>
 Fabian Luna scored 16 points to lead Cypress, which had won four in a row. 
Raymonds Miglinieks scored 22 for Riverside. 
</P>
