<HEADLINE>
<P>
IT'S CASTING DIRECTOR  
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Times continues to call casting directors casting agents ("South Carolina 
High School Teacher Wins Miss USA Contest," Section A, Feb. 12). There is no 
such thing as a casting agent.Casting directors do not represent actors, and we 
do not receive commissions (as do talent agents). Casting directors are hired 
by producers and directors. 
</P>
<P>
 And one more issue: In the review, " 'Twogether': Uncommonly Reflective Love 
Story" (Calendar, Feb. 11), which I cast, the film is given a wonderful review 
and the casting is mentioned, yet in the crew list costume design and sound 
editing are mentioned but no casting credit is given. Why does The Times 
continue to neglect credit for casting directors? 
</P>
<P>
 LORI COBE, C.S.A. 
</P>
<P>
 Lori Cobe Casting 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
