<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE QUESTION MAN ON ROBBERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Port Hueneme police said Friday that a man arrested after allegedly trying to 
rob an Oxnard dairy store may be the suspect sought in two earlier armed 
robberies. 
</P>
<P>
 James Kenneth Myers, 29, was arrested on Thursday after a clerk at Chase 
Bros.Dairy foiled his robbery attempt by refusing to give him money and then 
chasing him down the street, police said. The clerk said he believed Myers' gun 
was fake. 
</P>
<P>
 After Myers was arrested following a foot chase, police found his car parked a 
short distance from the dairy store on Channel Islands Boulevard. It matched a 
vehicle linked to a robbery the day before at the Waffle Factory in Port 
Hueneme, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Myers also resembled a composite sketch drawn from witness descriptions of the 
man who robbed the Video Store on North Ventura Road on Feb. 4, Port Hueneme 
Police Sgt. Jerry Beck said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
