<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: NORDHOFF KICKER LEACH SIGNS TO PLAY FOR DELAWARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANA HADDAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nordhoff High kicker Sean Leach has signed a letter of intent with Delaware, 
after he said the Fightin Blue Hens' coaching staff promised to make him the 
No. 1 kicker and punter next season. 
</P>
<P>
 Leach drew interest from Notre Dame, Syracuse, Oregon, Kansas State and 
several lower division schools.Washington invited him to walk on next fall. But 
Delaware was the only school to offer a full scholarship to Leach, named to the 
all-state medium schools division team by Cal-Hi Sports. USA Today ranked him 
second in the country among punters. 
</P>
<P>
 Leach said the Fighting Irish told him he was their No. 1 choice but later 
opted to "stick with Brian Ford." 
</P>
<P>
 Ford, who will be a sophomore next season, was given a scholarship by the 
Irish after he transferred from Vanderbilt. 
</P>
<P>
 Leach made seven of 11 field-goal attempts, 33 of 37 extra points and had a 
44.7-yard punting average, including a 77-yarder. 
</P>
<P>
 "I like the people and the campus at Delaware," Leach said. "It's a good 
atmosphere. Plus, they promised me I would punt and kick for four years, where 
at Notre Dame I'd always have to compete for a job." DANA HADDAD 
</P>
</TEXT>
